comment: OG is close to expected, FG is high though, should attenuate a bit more.
moved effic and it did take the OG up
switching to all vriess 2 romw, drops the srm and no more malt flavor needed from the base with the 20% other malts in there.
23 grams of dry for this, why is the OG low?  need to look at old recipe to confirm.
changed the grain to us 120, they didnt have any 150, going with single infusion, 150-152 goal
154 mash, dropped to 149 by the end, 60 minutes. pull 7-7.5
used c 120 US (instead of 150) and us choc 350 (instead of choc 425)
Very nice, more of a red thus time (lowwr l of the chocolate). Slightly lower the simcoe at 30, will lower the ibus as well into a good range as well, let more fruit and citrus shine.
has some hot alcohol for some reason, maybe it did get too hot during ferm. still tasty, piney goodness, once it warms you get a bit of hot alc though
